# Template System Rules
- Templates are code-first React components, not DB-driven ([about-templates.md](mdc:about-templates.md)).
- Each template must have: `index.tsx`, `template-config.ts`, `styles.ts`.
- All template config and props must match `@/lib/templates/template-types.ts`.
- Never add new template categories or config fields without updating the shared types.
- Test templates for edge runtime compatibility (no fs, only static imports).
- Optimize for mobile-first and performance; follow best practices for asset management and responsiveness.
